[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'everyone faces when they try to create a music video in Seed and S 2.0. One, how do I get my own face or an AI persona\'s face into the video when direct human face references can be rejected,'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'weakened, or interpreted inconsistently? Two, how do I achieve accurate lip synchronization? Three, how do I keep the original recording from being altered or reinterpreted by Seed and S?'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Four, how do I maintain strong character consistency across every shot? Well, I found the way. My way.'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; It\'s the sound of a man. The AA community has tested various'

[02:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'workarounds and until now one of the best options for lip sync and preserving the original audio has been uploading a black screen video with the original audio track embedded inside it. But we'

[02:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'found something better. Instead of creating a black screen video, create an MP4 file with a close-up still image of your face or your AI singer\'s face and'

[02:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'add your music track as the audio. If this is done properly, it can help with all four problems I just mentioned: face fidelity, character consistency, lip sync, and preserving the original track.'

[02:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Want to know how to do it correctly? Let me break it down for you. To do this, I\'m going to use Syn Labs 2.0 Omni, available at OpenArt AI platform, the sponsor of this video. To save yourself'

[03:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'frustration and lost credits, I suggest following the exact procedure that gave us consistently strong results. We took a clear close-up photo of my face using a mobile phone. If you do not'

[03:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'want to act as the lead singer, you can create a close-up image of your AI lead vocalist instead. We cut the song\'s audio track into 4 to 15-second parts, making sure each part contains a'

[03:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'complete vocal phrase or phrases whenever possible, so we don\'t cut the singer in the middle of a critical syllable. Each part must be cut to a whole second. For example, the segment'

[03:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'should be either 5 or 6 seconds long, not 5.3 seconds long. In our video editor of choice, we place the still image of my face on the timeline and added one of the MP3 audio segments as'

[03:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the audio track. The duration of the video, which is my still image, must exactly match the duration of the audio segment. We exported it as an MP4 file and repeated the same process for all'

[04:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'remaining song parts using the same image. Then we went to ChatGPT image tool. You can choose any AI model you use and created a character card showing me as a lead vocalist in a full body'

[04:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'shot including body proportions and the chosen outfit. We also created location cards that showed the interior set design for this music video. If you do not want to create these cards, you can'

[04:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'describe the character and location directly in the prompt. Well, we prefer to use cards for better precision. Now, we went to openart.ai, chose Cidence 2.0 Omni, and uploaded the reference files. The MP4 with the still'

[04:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'image and music, the original MP3 audio segment, and my character and location card. We input the prompt in the prompt section. Do not worry, I will show you the whole prompt structure that worked'

[04:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for us in a moment. We inserted the reference files in the correct places using the @ function. Then we generated the result, reviewed it, and repeated the process for all song segments until'

[05:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we had every shot ready for final editing. The exact same process was used for the video with our AI persona singer you watched at the beginning. I promised I would share our prompt structure for'

[05:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'music videos in Cidence 2.0 Omni. So, here it is. At the beginning of the prompt, we give Cidence the film DNA with a performance anchor. For this, we'

[05:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'use our still image plus audio MP4 file. This helps lock the lead vocalist face and give Cidence a precise time reference based on the original audio'

[05:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'segment. When we reference the audio track separately, pointing students to the MP3 file as the source for the audio and lip sync. Next, we use the add function to add the'

[05:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'character card and the location card. When we describe the action using timestamps and describe the camera movement and performance energy. If you created a storyboard, you can'

[06:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'also upload it as a reference, so you do not have to manually describe every visual detail in the prompt. In the section devoted to vocals, lyrics, and lip sync, we reference the'

[06:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'audio file again, add the exact lyrics to be lip-synced, and request a precise match between the mouth performance and the vocal. We also describe how the AI avatar or persona should perform the'

[06:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'song, including facial tension, breath pressure, neck muscle tension, microexpressions, and visible skin texture. Two more things are worth mentioning if'

[06:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you want this method to work smoothly. First, choose the right platform for students 2.0 Omni. It must allow you to upload video reference files long enough'

[07:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to cover at least one vocal phrase. In practice, 8 to 10 seconds videos are essential, and up to 15 seconds is preferable for greater flexibility. The platform should also allow you to'

[07:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'upload multiple reference files, including the MP4, the audio segment, and the character and location cards. This is why we use openart.ai for this workflow. Second, as always, start your'

[07:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'music video with a strong idea, then develop a storyboard and a shooting list. If you do not know how the shots are arranged, it is difficult to decide how long each MP4 segment should be.'

[07:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, that\'s the workflow. Simple but powerful. It helps you create music videos with more faithful real human or AI singer faces, cleaner lip sync,'

[07:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stronger character consistency, and an original music track that is not reinterpreted by SeeDance. It is not a one-button solution, but for us it made a real difference.'

